    "summary": "Convex exposes a Management REST API, an npm-based CLI, and a local MCP server launched from the CLI; all require Convex-issued credentials.",
    "description": "Convex is an open-source backend platform centered on a reactive database and TypeScript functions, with managed and self-hosted deployment options. It provides tooling to manage Convex projects and deployments and to expose project functionality to apps and AI tools.",
    "credentials": {
      "team_access_token": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "label": "Team access token",
        "generateUrl": "https://dashboard.convex.dev/team/settings/access-tokens",
        "setup": "In [Team Settings → Access Tokens](https://dashboard.convex.dev/team/settings/access-tokens), create a team-scoped access token for your Convex team. The [Platform APIs overview](https://docs.convex.dev/platform-apis/overview) says this token is used to manage your own projects, and the [Management API overview](https://docs.convex.dev/management-api/overview) says it is sent as a Bearer token in the `Authorization` header."
      },
      "oauth_app_token": {
        "type": "oauth2",
        "label": "OAuth application token",
        "generateUrl": "https://dashboard.convex.dev/team/settings/applications/oauth-apps",
        "setup": "Register an OAuth application in [Team Settings → OAuth Apps](https://dashboard.convex.dev/team/settings/applications/oauth-apps), then send users through the Convex OAuth authorization-code flow described in [OAuth Applications](https://docs.convex.dev/platform-apis/oauth-applications). Convex provides authorization endpoints at `https://dashboard.convex.dev/oauth/authorize/team` and `https://dashboard.convex.dev/oauth/authorize/project`, and the token endpoint is `https://api.convex.dev/oauth/token`. The resulting application token is used as a Bearer token for the Management API."
      },
      "convex_user_token": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "label": "Convex CLI user token",
        "setup": "Run `npx convex dev` interactively and log in on your device. The [CLI overview](https://docs.convex.dev/cli/overview) says first run prompts you to log in, and the [Deploy Keys](https://docs.convex.dev/cli/deploy-key-types) page says logging in stores a user token at `~/.convex/config.json`, which the CLI then uses automatically on that machine."
      },
      "convex_deploy_key": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "label": "Convex deploy key",
        "setup": "Create a deploy key via the [Create deploy key Management API](https://docs.convex.dev/management-api/create-deploy-key) or obtain one through your Convex deployment workflow, then set it in `CONVEX_DEPLOY_KEY`. The [Platform APIs overview](https://docs.convex.dev/platform-apis/overview) shows using `CONVEX_DEPLOY_KEY=\"YOUR_DEPLOY_KEY\" npx convex dev` / `npx convex deploy`, and the [Deploy Keys](https://docs.convex.dev/cli/deploy-key-types) page documents `CONVEX_DEPLOY_KEY` for non-interactive CLI use."
      }
    },
